ap9i658Qr68\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"     1Ôćĺ// Package agent provides interfaces and types for integrating with coding agents.\\n     2Ôćĺ// It abstracts agent-specific behavior (hooks, log parsing, session storage) so that\\n     3Ôćĺ// the same Strategy implementations can work with any coding agent.\\n     4Ôćĺpackage agent\\n     5Ôćĺ\\n     6Ôćĺimport (\\n     7Ôćĺ\\t\\\"io\\\"\\n     8Ôćĺ)\\n     9Ôćĺ\\n    10Ôćĺ// Agent defines the interface for interacting with a coding agent.\\n    11Ôćĺ// Each agent implementation (Claude Code, Cursor, Aider, etc.) converts its\\n    12Ôćĺ// native format to the normalized types defined in this package.\\n    13Ôćĺ//\\n    14Ôćĺ// The interface is organized into four groups:\\n    15Ôćĺ//\\n    16Ôćĺ//   - Identity (5 methods): Name, Type, Description, DetectPresence, ProtectedDirs\\n    17Ôćĺ//   - Event Mapping (2 methods): HookNames, ParseHookEvent\\n    18Ôćĺ//   - Transcript Storage (3 methods): ReadTranscript, ChunkTranscript, ReassembleTranscript\\n    19Ôćĺ//   - Legacy (8 methods): Will be moved to optional interfaces or removed in a future phase\\n    20Ôćĺtype Agent interface {\\n    21Ôćĺ\\t// --- Identity ---\\n    22Ôćĺ\\n    23Ôćĺ\\t// Name returns the agent registry key (e.g., \\\"claude-code\\\", \\\"gemini\\\")\\n    24Ôćĺ\\tName() AgentName\\n    25Ôćĺ\\n    26Ôćĺ\\t// Type returns the agent type identifier (e.g., \\\"Claude Code\\\", \\\"Gemini CLI\\\")\\n    27Ôćĺ\\t// This is stored in metadata and trailers.\\n    28Ôćĺ\\tType() AgentType\\n    29Ôćĺ\\n    30Ôćĺ\\t// Description returns a human-readable description for UI\\n    31Ôćĺ\\tDescription() string\\n    32Ôćĺ\\n    33Ôćĺ\\t// DetectPresence checks if this agent is configured in the repository\\n    34Ôćĺ\\tDetectPresence() (bool, error)\\n    35Ôćĺ\\n    36Ôćĺ\\t// ProtectedDirs returns repo-root-relative directories that should never be\\n    37Ôćĺ\\t// modified or deleted during rewind or other destructive operations.\\n    38Ôćĺ\\t// Examples: [\\\".claude\\\"] for Claude, [\\\".gemini\\\"] for Gemini.\\n    39Ôćĺ\\tProtectedDirs() []string\\n    40Ôćĺ\\n    41Ôćĺ\\t// --- Event Mapping ---\\n    42Ôćĺ\\n    43Ôćĺ\\t// HookNames returns the hook verbs this agent supports.\\n    44Ôćĺ\\t// These become subcommands under `entire hooks <agent>`.\\n    45Ôćĺ\\t// e.g., [\\\"stop\\\", \\\"user-prompt-submit\\\", \\\"session-start\\\", \\\"session-end\\\"]\\n    46Ôćĺ\\tHookNames() []string\\n    47Ôćĺ\\n    48Ôćĺ\\t// ParseHookEvent translates an agent-native hook into a normalized lifecycle Event.\\n    49Ôćĺ\\t// Returns nil if the hook has no lifecycle significance (e.g., pass-through hooks).\\n    50Ôćĺ\\t// This is the core contribution surface for new agent implementations.\\n    51Ôćĺ\\tParseHookEvent(hookName string, stdin io.Reader) (*Event, error)\\n    52Ôćĺ\\n    53Ôćĺ\\t// --- Transcript Storage ---\\n    54Ôćĺ\\n    55Ôćĺ\\t// ReadTranscript reads the raw transcript bytes for a session.\\n    56Ôćĺ\\tReadTranscript(sessionRef string) ([]byte, error)\\n    57Ôćĺ\\n    58Ôćĺ\\t// ChunkTranscript splits a transcript into chunks if it exceeds maxSize.\\n    59Ôćĺ\\t// Returns a slice of chunks. If the transcript fits in one chunk, returns single-element slice.\\n    60Ôćĺ\\t// The chunking is format-aware: JSONL splits at line boundaries, JSON splits message arrays.\\n    61Ôćĺ\\tChunkTranscript(content []byte, maxSize int) ([][]byte, error)\\n    62Ôćĺ\\n    63Ôćĺ\\t// ReassembleTranscript combines chunks back into a single transcript.\\n    64Ôćĺ\\t// Handles format-specific reassembly (JSONL concatenation, JSON message merging).\\n    65Ôćĺ\\tReassembleTranscript(chunks [][]byte) ([]byte, error)\\n    66Ôćĺ\\n    67Ôćĺ\\t// --- Legacy methods (will move to optional interfaces in Phase 4) ---\\n    68Ôćĺ\\n    69Ôćĺ\\t// GetHookConfigPath returns path to hook config file (empty if none).\\n    70Ôćĺ\\tGetHookConfigPath() string\\n    71Ôćĺ\\n    72Ôćĺ\\t// SupportsHooks returns true if agent supports lifecycle hooks.\\n    73Ôćĺ\\tSupportsHooks() bool\\n    74Ôćĺ\\n    75Ôćĺ\\t// ParseHookInput parses hook callback input from stdin.\\n    76Ôćĺ\\tParseHookInput(hookType HookType, reader io.Reader) (*HookInput, error)\\n    77Ôćĺ\\n    78Ôćĺ\\t// GetSessionID extracts session ID from hook input.\\n    79Ôćĺ\\tGetSessionID(input *HookInput) string\\n    80Ôćĺ\\n    81Ôćĺ\\t// GetSessionDir returns where agent stores session data for this repo.\\n    82Ôćĺ\\tGetSessionDir(repoPath string) (string, error)\\n    83Ôćĺ\\n    84Ôćĺ\\t// ResolveSessionFile returns the path to the session transcript file.\\n    85Ôćĺ\\tResolveSessionFile(sessionDir, agentSessionID string) string\\n    86Ôćĺ\\n    87Ôćĺ\\t// ReadSession reads session data from agent's storage.\\n    88Ôćĺ\\tReadSession(input *HookInput) (*AgentSession, error)\\n    89Ôćĺ\\n    90Ôćĺ\\t// WriteSession writes session data for resumption.\\n    91Ôćĺ\\tWriteSession(session *AgentSession) error\\n    92Ôćĺ\\n    93Ôćĺ\\t// FormatResumeCommand returns command to resume a session.\\n    94Ôćĺ\\tFormatResumeCommand(sessionID string) string\\n    95Ôćĺ}\\n    96Ôćĺ\\n    97Ôćĺ// HookSupport is implemented by agents with lifecycle hooks.\\n    98Ôćĺ// This optional interface allows agents like Claude Code and Cursor to\\n    99Ôćĺ// install and manage hooks that notify Entire of agent events.\\n   100Ôćĺtype HookSupport interface {\\n   101Ôćĺ\\tAgent\\n   102Ôćĺ\\n   103Ôćĺ\\t// InstallHooks installs agent-specific hooks.\\n   104Ôćĺ\\t// If localDev is true, hooks point to local development build.\\n   105Ôćĺ\\t// If force is true, removes existing Entire hooks before installing.\\n   106Ôćĺ\\t// Returns the number of hooks installed.\\n   107Ôćĺ\\tInstallHooks(localDev bool, force bool) (int, error)\\n   108Ôćĺ\\n   109Ôćĺ\\t// UninstallHooks removes installed hooks\\n   110Ôćĺ\\tUninstallHooks() error\\n   111Ôćĺ\\n   112Ôćĺ\\t// AreHooksInstalled checks if hooks are currently installed\\n   113Ôćĺ\\tAreHooksInstalled() bool\\n   114Ôćĺ\\n   115Ôćĺ\\t// GetSupportedHooks returns the hook types this agent supports\\n   116Ôćĺ\\tGetSupportedHooks() []HookType\\n   117Ôćĺ}\\n   118Ôćĺ\\n   119Ôćĺ// HookHandler is implemented by agents that define their own hook vocabulary.\\n   120Ôćĺ// HookNames() is now part of the core Agent interface.\\n   121Ôćĺ// This interface is kept for backward compatibility during migration.\\n   122Ôćĺtype HookHandler interface {\\n   123Ôćĺ\\tAgent\\n   124Ôćĺ\\n   125Ôćĺ\\t// GetHookNames returns the hook verbs this agent supports.\\n   126Ôćĺ\\tGetHookNames() []string\\n   127Ôćĺ}\\n   128Ôćĺ\\n   129Ôćĺ// FileWatcher is implemented by agents that use file-based detection.\\n   130Ôćĺ// Agents like Aider that don't support hooks can use file watching\\n   131Ôćĺ// to detect session activity.\\n   132Ôćĺtype FileWatcher interface {\\n   133Ôćĺ\\tAgent\\n   134Ôćĺ\\n   135Ôćĺ\\t// GetWatchPaths returns paths to watch for session changes\\n   136Ôćĺ\\tGetWatchPaths() ([]string, error)\\n   137Ôćĺ\\n   138Ôćĺ\\t// OnFileChange handles a detected file change and returns session info\\n   139Ôćĺ\\tOnFileChange(path string) (*SessionChange, error)\\n   140Ôćĺ}\\n   141Ôćĺ\\n   142Ôćĺ// TranscriptAnalyzer provides format-specific transcript parsing.\\n   143Ôćĺ// Agents that implement this get richer checkpoints (transcript-derived file lists,\\n   144Ôćĺ// prompts, summaries). Agents that don't still participate in the checkpoint lifecycle\\n   145Ôćĺ// via git-status-based file detection and raw transcript storage.\\n   146Ôćĺtype TranscriptAnalyzer interface {\\n   147Ôćĺ\\tAgent\\n   148Ôćĺ\\n   149Ôćĺ\\t// GetTranscriptPosition returns the current position (length) of a transcript.\\n   150Ôćĺ\\t// For JSONL formats (Claude Code), this is the line count.\\n   151Ôćĺ\\t// For JSON formats (Gemini CLI), this is the message count.\\n   152Ôćĺ\\t// Returns 0 if the file doesn't exist or is empty.\\n   153Ôćĺ\\tGetTranscript