5a7cf2\",\"version\":\"2.1.44\",\"gitBranch\":\"soph/agent-refactor\",\"slug\":\"snazzy-jingling-candy\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"type\":\"bash_progress\",\"output\":\"\",\"fullOutput\":\"\",\"elapsedTimeSeconds\":29,\"totalLines\":0,\"timeoutMs\":300000},\"toolUseID\":\"bash-progress-27\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_016dSsKjCdhqLahEeLDcuRnx\",\"uuid\":\"9d018512-b59c-4ffb-923d-6ee07aa0e793\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-18T02:15:05.036Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"9d018512-b59c-4ffb-923d-6ee07aa0e793\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/2\",\"sessionId\":\"9d47c125-80c3-421c-a4f6-e9ee685a7cf2\",\"version\":\"2.1.44\",\"gitBranch\":\"soph/agent-refactor\",\"slug\":\"snazzy-jingling-candy\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"type\":\"bash_progress\",\"output\":\"\",\"fullOutput\":\"\",\"elapsedTimeSeconds\":30,\"totalLines\":0,\"timeoutMs\":300000},\"toolUseID\":\"bash-progress-28\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_016dSsKjCdhqLahEeLDcuRnx\",\"uuid\":\"9fe8e973-e903-4915-96eb-dd332232716d\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-18T02:15:06.036Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"9fe8e973-e903-4915-96eb-dd332232716d\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/2\",\"sessionId\":\"9d47c125-80c3-421c-a4f6-e9ee685a7cf2\",\"version\":\"2.1.44\",\"gitBranch\":\"soph/agent-refactor\",\"slug\":\"snazzy-jingling-candy\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"assistant\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-18T02:15:06.223Z\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01M1T7FMdzQkBA35zCrLspqx\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01CmXL4qbAT5E8kM8pmcD2d6\",\"name\":\"Write\",\"input\":{\"file_path\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/2/docs/plans/review-agent-refactor-01.md\",\"content\":\"# Review 01 - Agent Refactor (PR #360)\\n\\n> Status: pending-dev\\n> Date: 2026-02-18\\n> Reviewer: Code Review Agent\\n> Verdict: APPROVE (with suggestions)\\n\\n## Scope\\n\\nBranch `soph/agent-refactor` vs `main`. 9 commits totalling +4254/-2379 lines across 47 files. The PR implements the plan from `PLAN.md`: replace per-agent handler files with a generic lifecycle dispatcher, unify state capture, rename Step/Checkpoint terminology, and extract Claude-specific PostTodo handling.\\n\\n## Previous Review Status\\n\\nNo prior reviews for this PR.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Verification: Deleted Files\\n\\n### hooks_claudecode_handlers.go (892 lines deleted)\\nAll functions from this file have been accounted for:\\n\\n| Old Function | New Location | Notes |\\n|---|---|---|\\n| `parseAndLogHookInput()` | Removed | Replaced by `ParseHookEvent` on agent |\\n| `captureInitialState()` | `lifecycle.go:handleLifecycleTurnStart` | Calls unified `CapturePrePromptState(ag, ...)` |\\n| `commitWithMetadata()` | `lifecycle.go:handleLifecycleTurnEnd` | Fully replaced by generic dispatcher |\\n| `handleClaudeCodePostTodo()` | `hooks_claudecode_posttodo.go:25` | Extracted as-is |\\n| `handleClaudeCodePreTask()` | `lifecycle.go:handleLifecycleSubagentStart` | Generic |\\n| `handleClaudeCodePostTask()` | `lifecycle.go:handleLifecycleSubagentEnd` | Generic |\\n| `handleClaudeCodeSessionStart()` | `lifecycle.go:handleLifecycleSessionStart` | Generic (was already shared via `handleSessionStartCommon`) |\\n| `handleClaudeCodeSessionEnd()` | `lifecycle.go:handleLifecycleSessionEnd` | Generic |\\n| `transitionSessionTurnEnd()` | `lifecycle.go:696` | Moved without functional change |\\n| `markSessionEnded()` | `lifecycle.go:724` | Moved without functional change |\\n| `waitForTranscriptFlush()` | `agent/claudecode/lifecycle.go:246` | Moved to agent package (correct - Claude-specific) |\\n| `checkStopSentinel()` | `agent/claudecode/lifecycle.go:271` | Moved to agent package (correct - Claude-specific) |\\n\\n**Verdict: No logic lost.**\\n\\n### hooks_geminicli_handlers.go (659 lines deleted)\\nAll functions accounted for:\\n\\n| Old Function | New Location | Notes |\\n|---|---|---|\\n| `handleGeminiSessionStart()` | `lifecycle.go:handleLifecycleSessionStart` | Generic |\\n| `handleGeminiSessionEnd()` | `lifecycle.go:handleLifecycleSessionEnd` | Generic |\\n| `handleGeminiBeforeAgent()` | `lifecycle.go:handleLifecycleTurnStart` | Generic |\\n| `handleGeminiAfterAgent()` | `lifecycle.go:handleLifecycleTurnEnd` | Generic |\\n| `handleGeminiPreCompress()` | `lifecycle.go:handleLifecycleCompaction` | Generic (new event type) |\\n| `handleGeminiBeforeTool/AfterTool/BeforeModel/AfterModel/BeforeToolSelection/Notification` | Removed - no-ops | Agent returns `nil` from `ParseHookEvent` for these pass-through hooks |\\n| `commitGeminiSession()` | `lifecycle.go:handleLifecycleTurnEnd` | Core logic merged into generic path |\\n| `createContextFileForGemini()` | `lifecycle.go:createContextFile` | Unified context file creation |\\n| `logFileChanges()` | `lifecycle.go:747` | Moved |\\n| `extractGeminiMetadata()` | Now uses `TranscriptAnalyzer` interface methods on `GeminiCLIAgent` | Correct decomposition |\\n\\n**Verdict: No logic lost.** The 12 Gemini pass-through hooks (before-tool, after-tool, etc.) that were no-ops requiring boilerplate handler functions are now elegantly handled by returning `nil` from `ParseHookEvent`.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Verification: New Architecture\\n\\n### Event Flow (Correct)\\n\\n```\\nAgent hook fired\\n  -> newAgentHookVerbCmdWithLogging (hook_registry.go:91)\\n     -> ag.ParseHookEvent(hookName, stdin)       # Agent translates native hook to Event\\n        -> If Event != nil: DispatchLifecycleEvent(ag, event)  # Generic dispatcher\\n        -> If nil + PostTodo: handleClaudeCodePostTodo()       # Claude-specific\\n        -> If nil otherwise: no-op                              # Pass-through hooks\\n```\\n\\n### DispatchLifecycleEvent Routing (Correct)\\n\\nAll 7 event types are routed:\\n- SessionStart -> handleLifecycleSessionStart\\n- TurnStart -> handleLifecycleTurnStart\\n- TurnEnd -> handleLifecycleTurnEnd\\n- Compaction -> handleLifecycleCompaction\\n- SessionEnd -> handleLifecycleSessionEnd\\n- SubagentStart -> handleLifecycleSubagentStart\\n- SubagentEnd -> handleLifecycleSubagentEnd\\n\\n### CapturePrePromptState Unification (Correct)\\n\\nThe old design had `CapturePrePromptState()` (Claude-specific, counted JSONL lines) and `CaptureGeminiPrePromptState()` (Gemini-specific, counted JSON messages). The new version at `state.go:92` uses the `TranscriptAnalyzer` interface:\\n\\n```go\\nif analyzer, ok := ag.(agent.TranscriptAnalyzer); ok && sessionRef != \\\"\\\" {\\n    pos, posErr := analyzer.GetTranscriptPosition(sessionRef)\\n    ...\\n    transcriptOffset = pos\\n}\\n```\\n\\nThis correctly delegates format-specific transcript position calculation to each agent while keeping the framework logic unified. The `PrePromptState` struct now uses a single `TranscriptOffset` field with backward-compatible migration from the old `StepTranscriptStart` and `StartMessageIndex` fields.\\n\\n### Strategy Interface Rename (Correct)\\n\\n- `SaveChanges` -> `SaveStep`\\n- `SaveTaskCheckpoint` -> `SaveTaskStep`\\n- `SaveContext` -> `StepContext`\\n- `TaskCheckpointContext` -> `TaskStepContext`\\n\\nVerified these propagate consistently through all strategy implementations, tests, integration tests, and CLAUDE.md documentation.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Findings\\n\\n### Critical (Must Fix)\\n\\nNone.\\n\\n### Important (Should Fix)\\n\\n1. **[PLAN.md - should not be merged to main]** `PLAN.md` is a 677-line design document added at the repo root. It was created as a planning artifact and should not be merged into `main`. It describes internal implementation decisions that are better captured in commit history or a docs directory. The file should either be deleted before merge, or moved to `docs/plans/` if intended to be kept.\\n\\n2. **[lifecycle.go:153 - maintidx nolint]** `handleLifecycleTurnEnd` has a `//nolint:maintidx` suppression with an explanation about \\\"sequential orchestration of 8 steps.\\\" While the function is justifiably complex (the TurnEnd handler is the core checkpoint creation path), the comment itself acknowledges 8 sequential steps. Consider whether extracting the \\\"metadata extraction\\\" phase (lines 219-263) into a helper would improve readability. Not blocking, but worth considering given this is brand-new code.\\n\\n3. **[lifecycle.go:570 - best-effort transcript parsing silenced]** In `handleLifecycleSubagentEnd`, the checkpoint UUID lookup uses triple-underscore error suppression:\\n   ```go\\n   mainLines, _, _ := parseTranscriptForCheckpointUUID(event.SessionRef)\\n   ```\\n   If the transcript file is unreadable here, the checkpoint UUID will silently be empty. This is acceptable as best-effort behavior, but a `logging.Warn` would help operators debug cases where subagent rewind fails because the UUID was missing.\\n\\n### Suggestions (Consider)\\n\\n1. **[agent/claudecode/lifecycle.go + agent/geminicli/lifecycle.go - readAndParse duplication]** Both agent packages define an identical `readAndParse[T]` generic function:\\n   ```go\\n   func readAndParse[T any](stdin io.Reader) (*T, error) {\\n       data, err := io.ReadAll(stdin)\\n       // ... identical implementation\\n   }\\n   ```\\n   Consider extracting this to the `agent` package as a shared utility. The function is only ~15 lines, so the duplication is minor, but given the project's explicit focus on duplication prevention this is worth noting.\\n\\n2. **[hooks_claudecode_posttodo.go:59-62 - ShouldSkipOnDefaultBranch]** The PostTodo handler calls `ShouldSkipOnDefaultBranch()` but the lifecycle dispatcher (`handleLifecycleTurnEnd`, `handleLifecycleSubagentEnd`) does not perform this check. This means the main lifecycle path would attempt to save steps/checkpoints even on the default branch. Verify this is intentional -- the strategy layer may handle this, but it is worth confirming the behavior is consistent.\\n\\n3. **[lifecycle.go:402-403 - auto-commit transcript position update]** The auto-commit strategy-specific transcript position update is gated by a string comparison:\\n   ```go\\n   if strat.Name() == strategy.StrategyNameAutoCommit && newTranscriptPosition > 0 {\\n   ```\\n   This is a code smell - the lifecycle dispatcher is aware of a specific strategy name. Consider adding an optional interface (e.g., `TranscriptPositionUpdater`) instead of the string check. Minor since it is isolated to one location.\\n\\n4. **[lifecycle_test.go - test coverage gaps for happy paths]** The lifecycle tests thoroughly cover error paths (nil agent, nil event, empty session IDs, empty transcripts, empty repositories). However, there are no unit-level tests for the full happy path of `handleLifecycleTurnEnd` (creating a real transcript, running through the full save flow). The integration tests cover this end-to-end, so this is not a blocker, but unit tests for the happy path would catch regressions faster.\\n\\n5. **[state.go:65-82 - normalizePrePromptState migration chain]** The three-level migration chain (`LastTranscriptLineCount` -> `StepTranscriptStart` -> `TranscriptOffset`) is well-documented and tested. Consider adding a code comment noting when these deprecated fields can be removed (e.g., \\\"Safe to remove after version X\\\" or \\\"After all state files have been rotated\\\").\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Praise\\n\\n- **Excellent architectural decomposition.** The inversion from \\\"agent handler calls framework\\\" to \\\"framework dispatcher calls agent\\\" is the right pattern. The `ParseHookEvent` method on each agent is the perfect contribution surface -- a new agent implementer only needs to map their hooks to 7 event types.\\n\\n- **TranscriptAnalyzer as optional interface.** The decision to make transcript analysis optional (vs. core) was well-reasoned. Agents that cannot parse their transcripts still participate via git-status-based file detection. The framework gracefully degrades.\\n\\n- **Backward-compatible state migration.** The `normalizePrePromptState()` function correctly handles state files written by older CLI versions with three different deprecated field names. Each migration path is individually tested.\\n\\n- **Thorough integration test updates.** The integration tests were updated for the `SaveChanges` -> `SaveStep` rename, and the core integration test suite passes (56.9s, all green). The test environment's `SimulateStop` helper correctly drives through the new lifecycle path.\\n\\n- **Clean removal of 1551 lines of duplicated handler code.** The old Claude and Gemini handlers duplicated the same ~300-line framework orchestration pattern. The new lifecycle dispatcher eliminates this entirely.\\n\\n- **EventCompaction properly modeled.** The addition of `EventCompaction` to the session phase state machine with correct transitions from all three phases (ACTIVE, IDLE, ENDED) fills a gap that existed before this PR.\\n\\n- **PostTodo extraction is well-scoped.** The Claude-specific PostTodo handler is cleanly extracted to its own file with a clear header comment explaining why it is not part of the generic dispatcher.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Summary\\n\\n- **Overall assessment:** APPROVE\\n- **Key concerns:** PLAN.md should be removed before merge; the `readAndParse` duplication across agent packages should be addressed; consider logging the silenced transcript parse error in SubagentEnd.\\n- **Estimated effort to address feedback:** 15-30 minutes\\n\\nThis is a well-executed structural refactor that eliminates significant code duplication (~1551 lines of handler code removed), introduces a clean plugin surface for new agents, and maintains full backward compatibility. All unit tests (cached, clean) and integration tests (56.9s, passing) verify the refactor. Lint is clean (0 issues). No logic was lost from the deleted handler files. The Step/Checkpoint terminology rename is consistently applied across all 47 changed files.\\n\"},\"cal