538-542] `handleLifecycleSubagentEnd` uses nil `preState` without guard after error**\\n    31Ôćĺ\\n    32Ôćĺ`LoadPreTaskState` returns `(*PreTaskState, error)` and can return `(nil, someError)` when the state file exists but is corrupt. When that happens, the code logs a warning but calls `preState.PreUntrackedFiles()` on the next line:\\n    33Ôćĺ\\n    34Ôćĺ```go\\n    35ÔćĺpreState, err := LoadPreTaskState(event.ToolUseID)\\n    36Ôćĺif err != nil {\\n    37Ôćĺ    fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \\\"Warning: failed to load pre-task state: %v\\\\n\\\", err)\\n    38Ôćĺ}\\n    39Ôćĺchanges, err := DetectFileChanges(preState.PreUntrackedFiles())\\n    40Ôćĺ```\\n    41Ôćĺ\\n    42ÔćĺThe `PreUntrackedFiles()` method on `PreTaskState` (in `state.go:379`) does have a nil receiver guard, so this will not panic. However, the nil receiver returns `nil` (not `[]string{}`), which tells `DetectFileChanges` to include ALL untracked files as \\\"new\\\" -- every pre-existing untracked file in the repo would be falsely reported as a new file created by the subagent.\\n    43Ôćĺ\\n    44ÔćĺBy contrast, `handleLifecycleTurnEnd` at lines 294-298 correctly guards this case:\\n    45Ôćĺ\\n    46Ôćĺ```go\\n    47Ôćĺvar preUntrackedFiles []string\\n    48Ôćĺif preState != nil {\\n    49Ôćĺ    fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \\\"Pre-prompt state: %d pre-existing untracked files\\\\n\\\", len(preState.UntrackedFiles))\\n    50Ôćĺ    preUntrackedFiles = preState.PreUntrackedFiles()\\n    51Ôćĺ}\\n    52Ôćĺ```\\n    53Ôćĺ\\n    54Ôćĺ**Suggested fix:** Match the pattern from `handleLifecycleTurnEnd`:\\n    55Ôćĺ\\n    56Ôćĺ```go\\n    57ÔćĺpreState, err := LoadPreTaskState(event.ToolUseID)\\n    58Ôćĺif err != nil {\\n    59Ôćĺ    fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \\\"Warning: failed to load pre-task state: %v\\\\n\\\", err)\\n    60Ôćĺ}\\n    61Ôćĺvar preUntrackedFiles []string\\n    62Ôćĺif preState != nil {\\n    63Ôćĺ    preUntrackedFiles = preState.PreUntrackedFiles()\\n    64Ôćĺ}\\n    65Ôćĺchanges, err := DetectFileChanges(preUntrackedFiles)\\n    66Ôćĺ```\\n    67Ôćĺ\\n    68ÔćĺThis is functionally equivalent for the nil case (both return nil from `PreUntrackedFiles()`), but makes the intent explicit and consistent with `handleLifecycleTurnEnd`.\\n    69Ôćĺ\\n    70Ôćĺ---\\n    71Ôćĺ\\n    72Ôćĺ**2. [hook_registry.go:114-115] Dead assignment with nolint suppression**\\n    73Ôćĺ\\n    74Ôćĺ```go\\n    75ÔćĺstrategyName := unknownStrategyName //nolint:ineffassign,wastedassign // already present in codebase\\n    76ÔćĺstrategyName = GetStrategy().Name()\\n    77Ôćĺ```\\n    78Ôćĺ\\n    79ÔćĺThe nolint comment says \\\"already present in codebase,\\\" but this is the file being modified in this PR. The initial assignment to `unknownStrategyName` is immediately overwritten and never read -- if `GetStrategy().Name()` panics, the initial value provides no fallback because the panic happens before `strategyName` is used. This should be simplified to:\\n    80Ôćĺ\\n    81Ôćĺ```go\\n    82ÔćĺstrategyName := GetStrategy().Name()\\n    83Ôćĺ```\\n    84Ôćĺ\\n    85Ôćĺ---\\n    86Ôćĺ\\n    87Ôćĺ**3. [lifecycle.go:402-403] Strategy-specific logic hardcoded in generic dispatcher**\\n    88Ôćĺ\\n    89Ôćĺ```go\\n    90Ôćĺif strat.Name() == strategy.StrategyNameAutoCommit && newTranscriptPosition > 0 {\\n    91Ôćĺ    updateAutoCommitTranscriptPosition(sessionID, newTranscriptPosition)\\n    92Ôćĺ}\\n    93Ôćĺ```\\n    94Ôćĺ\\n    95ÔćĺThe lifecycle dispatcher is designed to be strategy-agnostic, routing events through interfaces like `TurnEndHandler` and `SessionInitializer`. This line breaks that pattern by checking for a specific strategy by name. The auto-commit transcript position update should be handled through an optional interface or within the `TurnEndHandler` dispatch, not via a name-based branch in the generic dispatcher.\\n    96Ôćĺ\\n    97Ôćĺ**Suggested fix:** Add a `TranscriptPositionUpdater` optional interface to the strategy package:\\n    98Ôćĺ\\n    99Ôćĺ```go\\n   100Ôćĺtype TranscriptPositionUpdater interface {\\n   101Ôćĺ    UpdateTranscriptPosition(sessionID string, position int) error\\n   102Ôćĺ}\\n   103Ôćĺ```\\n   104Ôćĺ\\n   105ÔćĺThen in the dispatcher:\\n   106Ôćĺ```go\\n   107Ôćĺif updater, ok := strat.(strategy.TranscriptPositionUpdater); ok && newTranscriptPosition > 0 {\\n   108Ôćĺ    updater.UpdateTranscriptPosition(sessionID, newTranscriptPosition)\\n   109Ôćĺ}\\n   110Ôćĺ```\\n   111Ôćĺ\\n   112Ôćĺ---\\n   113Ôćĺ\\n   114Ôćĺ**4. [lifecycle.go:88-90] `event.ResponseMessage` silently overrides computed banner including concurrent session count**\\n   115Ôćĺ\\n   116Ôćĺ```go\\n   117Ôćĺ// Build informational message\\n   118Ôćĺmessage := \\\"\\\\n\\\\nPowered by Entire:\\\\n  This conversation will be linked to your next commit.\\\"\\n   119Ôćĺ\\n   120Ôćĺ// Check for concurrent sessions and append count if any\\n   121Ôćĺstrat := GetStrategy()\\n   122Ôćĺif concurrentChecker, ok := strat.(strategy.ConcurrentSessionChecker); ok {\\n   123Ôćĺ    if count, err := concurrentChecker.CountOtherActiveSessionsWithCheckpoints(event.SessionID); err == nil && count > 0 {\\n   124Ôćĺ        message += fmt.Sprintf(\\\"\\\\n  %d other active conversation(s)...\\\", count)\\n   125Ôćĺ    }\\n   126Ôćĺ}\\n   127Ôćĺ\\n   128Ôćĺ// Output informational message\\n   129Ôćĺif event.ResponseMessage != \\\"\\\" {\\n   130Ôćĺ    message = event.ResponseMessage\\n   131Ôćĺ}\\n   132Ôćĺ```\\n   133Ôćĺ\\n   134ÔćĺIf `ResponseMessage` is set, the concurrent session warning computed on lines 80-85 is silently discarded. If this is intentional (agent-provided message takes full precedence), add a comment explaining that. If not, the `ResponseMessage` should be appended or the concurrent session logic should be skipped when `ResponseMessage` is set (to avoid unnecessary work).\\n   135Ôćĺ\\n   136Ôćĺ### Suggestions (Consider)\\n   137Ôćĺ\\n   138Ôćĺ**5. [lifecycle.go:154, 260 lines] `handleLifecycleTurnEnd` is long and has a `maintidx` nolint