ent)\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Scope\\n\\nThis review focuses on the specific areas requested:\\n1. **Strategy interface rename**: `SaveChanges` -> `SaveStep`, `SaveTaskCheckpoint` -> `SaveTaskStep`, `SaveContext` -> `StepContext`, `TaskCheckpointContext` -> `TaskStepContext`\\n2. **Consistency check**: Whether all references to old names are gone\\n3. **Behavioral changes**: Whether any non-rename changes snuck in\\n4. **EventCompaction**: New event in the session phase state machine\\n\\nAll unit tests pass. All integration tests pass. Lint clean. (Verified via `mise run test:ci` and `mise run lint`.)\\n\\n---\\n\\n## New Findings\\n\\n### Critical (Must Fix)\\n\\n**1. [/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/2/cmd/entire/cli/lifecycle.go:542] Nil `preState` -- third review flagging this**\\n\\nThis was flagged in review-01 (#6) and review-02 (#1) and remains unfixed. The behavioral consequence: when `LoadPreTaskState` returns `(nil, error)`, `DetectFileChanges(nil)` will treat every untracked file in the repository as newly created by the subagent, leading to inflated file change lists in the task checkpoint. This can cause large, incorrect checkpoints that include files the subagent never touched.\\n\\n```go\\n// Line 538-542 of /Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/2/cmd/entire/cli/lifecycle.go\\npreState, err := LoadPreTaskState(event.ToolUseID)\\nif err != nil {\\n    fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \\\"Warning: failed to load pre-task state: %v\\\\n\\\", err)\\n}\\nchanges, err := DetectFileChanges(preState.PreUntrackedFiles())  // nil preState -> all untracked files reported as new\\n```\\n\\n**Fix**: Apply the same guard pattern used at lines 294-298:\\n```go\\nvar preUntrackedFiles []string\\nif preState != nil {\\n    preUntrackedFiles = preState.PreUntrackedFiles()\\n}\\nchanges, err := DetectFileChanges(preUntrackedFiles)\\n```\\n\\n### Important (Should Fix)\\n\\n**2. Stale comments still reference `SaveChanges` instead of `SaveStep` (8 occurrences)**\\n\\nThe rename of me